annotationA: Defective proventriculus (Dve) is a transcriptional repressor that binds to the K50 site. Dve roles include developmental patterning, cell-type specification, and functional differentiation
annotationB: Death associated molecule related to Mch2 caspase (Damm) is one of the seven members of the caspase family of cysteine proteases. Damm overexpression induces cell death; Belongs to the peptidase C14A family
